excerpt: Sturdy castle of Boulogne counts, now housing archeology, local history & fine arts collections.
detail_description: Château de Boulogne-sur-Mer, located in the fortified upper town of Ville Fortifiée, is a historic site that houses the Chateau-Musee de Boulogne. This museum showcases archeological findings, local history artifacts, and fine art collections. The castle dates back to the 1200s and has undergone significant changes due to artillery advancements in the 16th and 17th centuries.
name: Château de Boulogne-sur-Mer

excerpt: Boulogne-sur-Mer is a city, known as a major fishing port, on the north coast of France. By the port, Nausicaá is a huge aquarium with thousands of marine species. In the fortified old town, Notre-Dame Basilica has an ornate crypt. The city’s 12th-century belfry was the keep of a Norman-era castle. Ancient Egyptian and Greek artifacts are on display at the Castle Museum, which is set within a 13th-century chateau.
detail_description: Boulogne-sur-Mer, located on the north coast of France, is a city renowned for its major fishing port and rich history. The fortified old town features attractions such as Notre-Dame Basilica with its ornate crypt and the 12th-century belfry that was once part of a Norman-era castle. The Castle Museum showcases ancient Egyptian and Greek artifacts within a 13th-century chateau.
name: Boulogne-sur-Mer

excerpt: Opened in 1950, this busy, tucked-away restaurant in the port serves fresh-caught fish & seafood.
detail_description: Le Chatillon is a bustling restaurant located in the port area of Boulogne-sur-Mer, France. Since its establishment in 1950, it has been a popular spot for locals and tourists seeking fresh seafood. Tucked away near the industrial district, the restaurant is known for serving freshly caught fish and seafood. Despite its unassuming exterior, Le Chatillon is a hidden gem that attracts people from the seafood industry as well as visitors who have heard about it through word-of-mouth.
name: Le Chatillon

detail_description: The Boulogne-sur-Mer Fish Market, located on Quai Gambetta near Pont Marguet, is a bustling spot where fishermen unload their catch at 7:00 am. With over 70 types of fish and seafood available for purchase, visitors can even handle live crabs and lobsters. Additionally, the nearby food market offers cheeses and charcuteries for those looking to take home local delicacies.
name: Boulogne-sur-Mer Fish Market

detail_description: Casa San Martín, located in Boulogne-sur-Mer, is a museum that was once the residence of General José de San Martín, an Argentine military leader who played a crucial role in the liberation of Argentina, Chile, and Peru. The museum showcases the general's personal possessions and offers insights into his life and achievements. Visitors can explore the historical significance of this site and gain a deeper understanding of 19th-century Argentina and France through guided tours.
name: Casa San Martín

detail_description: The Crypte de la Basilique Notre-Dame in Boulogne-sur-Mer is a captivating historical site that offers a unique glimpse into the past. Originally built as a church and later transformed into a cathedral, this impressive structure stands tall at 100 meters, overlooking the city. While some may find the basilica's 19th-century architecture less appealing, it sits atop ancient Roman foundations, connecting visitors to centuries of history.
name: Crypte de la Basilique Notre-Dame

excerpt: Popular sand beach offering rentals of deck chairs, a summer library, beach volleyball & more.
detail_description: Plage de Boulogne-sur-Mer is a popular sandy beach that offers various amenities such as deck chair rentals, a summer library, and beach volleyball. It is located in the heart of the old town near Notre Dame Cathedral. The area also boasts gastronomic delights and modern dining experiences with spacious terraces for warm weather months. Visitors can explore nearby natural sights like Ephemere Garden and religious buildings such as Notre Dame de Boulogne Cathedral.
name: Plage de Boulogne-sur-Mer

detail_description: Port de Boulogne-sur-Mer is a bustling city within the city, serving as France's top fishing port with a fleet of nearly 150 boats. The return of the fleet sets the rhythm of life here, bringing in over 70 different species of fish daily for auction. For a stunning view, head to the hill overlooking the port and take in the sailors' cemetery, which is both beautiful and poignant.
name: Port de Boulogne-sur-Mer

excerpt: Aquarium with a touch pool, sharks, sea lions & penguins, plus tropical lagoon with colorful coral.
detail_description: Nausicaa Centre National De La Mer, located in Boulogne-sur-Mer, France, is a renowned marine center that offers an immersive experience for visitors to discover the wonders of the sea. Since its opening in 1991, it has become one of the most popular tourist attractions in northern France. The center features various aquariums and terrariums showcasing a wide range of marine life, including sharks, sea lions, penguins, and a touch pool.
name: Nausicaá Centre National De La Mer

detail_description: The Basilica of Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception at Boulogne-sur-Mer is situated in the Pas-de-Calais region, France. It is housed in the historic castle of Aumont, dating back to the 13th century and classified as a Historical Monument. The basilica's construction began in the 19th century, replacing an earlier church that was destroyed during turbulent times. The cathedral boasts stunning Renaissance architecture and is surrounded by charming gardens.
name: Basilica of Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception at Boulogne-sur-Mer

detail_description: Ville Fortifiée is a fascinating historical site with origins dating back to the 1300s. Inspired by Roman design, this 1.5-kilometer wall offers a captivating walk alongside a simple castrum, featuring 20 towers, stone passageways, gates, a moat, and an impressive arched bridge connecting to the Chateau Comtal. The site provides ample opportunities for exploration and discovery of its rich history and architectural marvels.
name: Ville Fortifiée

detail_description: As you make your way to Capécure, the industrial heart of Boulogne-sur-Mer, you'll be greeted by the enticing scent of the sea wafting through the air, hinting at a delightful culinary experience ahead. One gem in this area is Le Chatillon, a charming restaurant that has been serving seafood lovers since 1950. This spot has become a beloved gathering place for locals and those in the seafood trade alike, often discovered through word-of-mouth recommendations.
name: Capécure

detail_description: If you're in search of some delightful retail therapy, Rue Victor Hugo is a fantastic destination to explore. This charming street is lined with an array of shops that cater to various tastes and preferences. While you’re there, don’t miss the vibrant market at Place Dalton, which takes place every Wednesday and Friday morning.
name: Rue Victor Hugo

excerpt: Saint-Martin-Boulogne is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de-France region of France. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Saint-Martin-Boulogne is a charming commune located in the Pas-de-Calais department of the Hauts-de-France region in France. Situated conveniently near the A16 highway, it offers easy access for travelers. The area is well-connected with a main train station just 3.4 km away and accessible via bus lines L and D, as well as taxi services.
name: Saint-Martin-Boulogne

excerpt: Understated units with balconies in a down-to-earth apartment hotel offering river views.
name: Résidence La Marina - Evancy Boulogne-sur-Mer
address: Quai Chanzy Boulevard du, 62200 Boulogne-sur-Mer, France

excerpt: Warm rooms in a refined hotel with a sleek restaurant & bar, plus an indoor pool & a hammam.
detail_description: Located in the heart of Boulogne-sur-Mer, Hôtel La Matelote is a refined 4-star hotel offering warm rooms and a sleek restaurant and bar. It's conveniently situated within a 5-minute walk from Musee Maison de la Beuriere and Plage de Boulogne-sur-Mer. The hotel boasts an indoor pool, a hammam, and a sauna for guests to enjoy. Additionally, free Wi-Fi access is available throughout the property.
name: Hôtel La Matelote

detail_description: Nausicaa is a must-visit aquarium located in the region, highly recommended for divers, children, and everyone. The well-organized route makes it ideal for a family outing and enjoyable for all ages. Visitors can even go behind the scenes upon request for a fee. The aquarium's stunning exhibits mesmerize visitors, providing an immersive experience with beautiful animals and their habitats. Additionally, Nausicaa offers entertainment with sea lions, creating a unique feeling of being in the water.
name: Nausicaa

detail_description: Remparts de Boulogne-sur-Mer is a charming place that offers a glimpse into the city's traditions and history. The herring king festival, held annually in September, allows visitors to savor fresh herring grilled on giant barbecues and enjoy Beaujolais wine. The well-preserved ramparts and old town walls are surrounded by impressive architectural buildings, creating an atmosphere of times gone by.
name: Remparts de Boulogne-sur-Mer

detail_description: Boulogne-sur-Mer is a charming destination, perfect for a holiday getaway. This artistic city offers a delightful atmosphere for travelers to explore.
name: Boulogne-sur-Mer

detail_description: La Kabane de Plage is a delightful beachfront restaurant that perfectly captures the essence of coastal dining. After a refreshing swim, there's nothing quite like indulging in their exquisite seafood offerings, such as expertly prepared turbot paired with beetroot and chorizo or seasonal scallops. For dessert, don't miss the spectacular crepes Suzette flambéed right before your eyes!
name: La Kabane de Plage

detail_description: Boulogne-sur-Mer is a charming destination that offers a delightful mix of history and marine wonders. The old walled city center captivates visitors with its picturesque streets and inviting restaurants, making it an ideal spot for a leisurely day trip. A highlight is the Nausicaa aquarium, which promises an unforgettable experience, especially on rainy days when outdoor activities may be limited. However, while the town has its attractions, some travelers note that it suffers from industrial areas and signs of neglect.
name: Boulogne sur mer

detail_description: When you find yourself in the charming coastal town of Wimereux, make sure to visit L'Atelier des Mets. This delightful eatery is celebrated not only for its exquisite cuisine but also for its breathtaking panoramic views that enhance your dining experience. Guests rave about the quality and presentation of each dish, with flavors that leave a lasting impression. The attentive staff ensures every need is met, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere.
name: L'Atelier des Mets
address: 4 Pl. de l'Église, 62480 Le Portel, France

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Boulogne-sur-Mer, the Gare de Boulogne-Ville stands as a vital hub for travelers seeking to explore not only this charming coastal city but also major destinations across France and beyond. This bustling train station connects visitors with various cities, making it an essential stop on any journey.
name: Gare de Boulogne-Ville

detail_description: If you're planning a trip to Boulogne-sur-Mer, consider Europcar for your car rental needs. This reputable agency offers a variety of vehicles at competitive prices starting from around 40 per day, making it easy to find the perfect ride for your adventure. The service is highly praised by customers who appreciate the quality and reliability of their vehicles.
name: Europcar Boulogne Sur Mer

detail_description: When visiting Boulogne-sur-Mer, Avis Location Voiture Boulogne is a great option for car rentals. This service offers a variety of vehicles to suit your travel needs, with prices starting around 40 per day based on the type of car and how long you plan to rent it. The experience is known for its quick and efficient service, complemented by a warm welcome from the staff.
name: Avis Location Voiture Boulogne
address: Gare Sncf, Bd Voltaire, 62200 Boulogne-sur-Mer, France

detail_description: Promenade Charles Dickens - Les remparts in Boulogne-sur-Mer offers a captivating experience of strolling along the best-preserved ramparts in northern France. Built between 1227-1231, this historical site provides a glimpse into the past and stunning views of the city from its walkway. The well-maintained trail is perfect for a leisurely walk, with numerous benches to rest and admire the panoramic scenery.
name: Promenade Charles Dickens - Les remparts

detail_description: Éphémère Garden, located at place Godefroy de Bouillon, is a temporary garden attraction that captivates visitors from late June to mid-October. Each year, the garden presents a new theme, such as music in 2022. The gardens are surrounded by charming restaurants and offer free access with classical music playing in the background. Visitors can expect to be enchanted by the colorful and vibrant displays that engage all senses.
name: Éphémère Garden
address: 3 Pl. Godefroy de Bouillon, 62200 Boulogne-sur-Mer, France

detail_description: The École-Musée de Boulogne-sur-Mer is an extraordinary institution that transports visitors back in time and evokes nostalgic memories, regardless of their educational background. This hidden gem situated in the heart of Boulogne Sur Mer offers a remarkable collection presented with utmost attention to detail. The warm and friendly reception upon arrival further enhances the overall experience. It's a highly recommended destination for anyone seeking an enjoyable and captivating visit.
name: École-Musée de Boulogne-sur-Mer
address: 2 Rue de l'Ancien Rivage, 62200 Boulogne-sur-Mer, France

detail_description: House of Beurière is a small but impressive museum located in an original fisherman's house in the old fisherman's quarter of Boulogne-sur-Mer. The museum offers a glimpse into the daily life of families at the beginning of the 20th century through its display of furniture, possessions, engravings, and clothing. Visitors can explore this authentic setting and gain insight into the historical lifestyle on this coast.
name: House of Beurière

detail_description: The Casino Golden Palace Boulogne-sur-Mer is a popular recreational facility that offers a variety of entertainment options. Located in Boulogne-sur-Mer, this recreation center provides numerous activities for visitors looking to have a good time. With its wide range of games and amenities, the Casino Golden Palace ensures an enjoyable experience for all patrons. From gaming tables to slot machines, this establishment caters to diverse preferences and interests. Additionally, the casino features live performances and shows that enhance the overall atmosphere.
name: Casino Golden Palace Boulogne-sur-Mer
address: Pl. de la République, 62200 Boulogne-sur-Mer, France

detail_description: Dedicated to Auguste Mariette, one of the pioneering Egyptologists, the Statue of Auguste Mariette is a significant tourist attraction located in Boulogne-Sur-Mer. Born in 1821 and passing away in Bulak (near Cairo) in 1881, Mariette conducted numerous excavations and established the renowned Egyptian Museum in Cairo. As a tribute to his contributions, his statue stands prominently atop a pyramid-like structure, symbolizing his achievements.
name: Statue Auguste Mariette

detail_description: Discover the captivating street art of Boulogne Sur Mer with the Street-Art, trompe l'oeil de Borondo tour. This self-guided tour offers five different routes through the city, each showcasing a unique side of Boulogne. You can pick up a map at the tourist center and explore magnificent works of art adorning the walls.
name: Street-Art, trompe l'oeil de Borondo

detail_description: L'Embarcadère is a new convention and entertainment center in Boulogne-sur-Mer, which recently hosted the Video Mapping Festival. The venue received high praise for its beautiful rooms and comfortable atmosphere during the Poulpaphone event. It has been described as a great performance hall that brings luck to Boulogne by being able to welcome artists.
name: L'Embarcadère
